physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Flushed, dehydrated, vomiting persistently. Partial-thickness burn on the left side of the back in the distribution of T8 covering about 7% of the body surface. Elevated white cell count and low serum potassium. Ketonuria. Chronic constipation.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Vomiting stopped abruptly 8 days after admission, but another episode commenced before discharge and lasted 4 days, confirmed to be associated with a rise in porphyrins.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Patient was well, pregnancy was progressing normally.
